TY  - JOUR
T1  - Trust Repair After An Organization-Level Failure
AU  - Gillespie, Nicole
AU  - Dietz, Graham
Y1  - 2009/01/01
PY  - 2009
DA  - 2009/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2009.35713319
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2009.35713319
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 127
EP  - 145
VL  - 34
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We propose a systemic, multilevel framework for understanding trust repair at the organizational level. Drawing on systems theory, we theorize how each component of an organization's system shapes employees? perceptions of the organization's trustworthiness and can contribute to failures and effective trust repair. We distinguish the framework from prior work grounded in dyadic assumptions and propose underlying principles and a four-stage process for organizational trust repair. Finally, we explore the implications for research and practice.
AB  - We propose a systemic, multilevel framework for understanding trust repair at the organizational level. Drawing on systems theory, we theorize how each component of an organization's system shapes employees? perceptions of the organization's trustworthiness and can contribute to failures and effective trust repair. We distinguish the framework from prior work grounded in dyadic assumptions and propose underlying principles and a four-stage process for organizational trust repair. Finally, we explore the implications for research and practice.
