TY  - JOUR
T1  - Managing Intractable Identity Conflicts
AU  - Fiol, C. Marlene
AU  - Pratt, Michael G.
AU  - O'Connor, Edward J.
Y1  - 2009/01/01
PY  - 2009
DA  - 2009/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2009.35713276
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2009.35713276
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 32
EP  - 55
VL  - 34
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Identity is often at the heart of ongoing intergroup conflicts in organizations. Drawing from theories of conflict management, social identity, and organizational identification, we develop the intractable identity conflict resolution model, which delineates a multiphase process by which the conflicting parties? identities shift in order to permit eventual intergroup harmony.
AB  - Identity is often at the heart of ongoing intergroup conflicts in organizations. Drawing from theories of conflict management, social identity, and organizational identification, we develop the intractable identity conflict resolution model, which delineates a multiphase process by which the conflicting parties? identities shift in order to permit eventual intergroup harmony.
