TY  - JOUR
T1  - Reparing Relationships Within and Between Organizations: Building A Conceptual Foundation
AU  - Dirks, Kurt T.
AU  - Lewicki, Roy J.
AU  - Zaheer, Akbar
Y1  - 2009/01/01
PY  - 2009
DA  - 2009/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2009.35713285
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2009.35713285
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 68
EP  - 84
VL  - 34
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - How can relationships be repaired after being damaged? There is a small but growing body of work on the topic from a number of different disciplinary perspectives using different theoretical lenses and at different levels of analysis. We begin by examining the existing streams of work on relationship repair and organizing them into a conceptual framework. We then consider four questions that probe assumptions or overlooked issues in existing research with the intent of moving toward a more comprehensive conceptual foundation.
AB  - How can relationships be repaired after being damaged? There is a small but growing body of work on the topic from a number of different disciplinary perspectives using different theoretical lenses and at different levels of analysis. We begin by examining the existing streams of work on relationship repair and organizing them into a conceptual framework. We then consider four questions that probe assumptions or overlooked issues in existing research with the intent of moving toward a more comprehensive conceptual foundation.
